{
  "texts": [
    "Two more examples of light curves (top panels) and spectra (bottom panels) for two sources contained in the eRASS1 Main catalogue, generated from the released source products.",
    "On the left hand side, we show the light curve and spectrum of the bright star AD Leo (1eRASS J101935.6+195211; DETUID: em01_155069_020_ML00001_011_c010).",
    "The light curve (top left) is shown with the original 10s binning.",
    "The spectrum (bottom left) is fitted with a multi-temperature thermal collisionally-ionised plasma emission model (apec+apec+apec, with tied abundances).",
    "On the right hand side, we show the light curve and spectrum of SMSS J114447.770-430859.3, the most luminous QSO of the last 9 Gyr (Onken et al."
  ]
}